{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/punc/punc-01009/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PUNC-01009"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:10:09"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Punch-Drunk Love"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}}],"summary":{"none":["Vertical stripes of shades of pink and red."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-01009/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PUNC-01009","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-01009/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PUNC-01009"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-01009/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-01009/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-01009/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-01009/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-01009/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-01009/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-01009/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-01009/canvas/1/35dd78ec-140a-47ca-838f-b80a316689ff","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2025-08-14T19:29:34.774Z","creator":"Olivia Flores","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>PTA first encountered the work of artist Jeremy Blake (1971-2007) at the San Francisco Museum of Modern Art (SFMOMA) (<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" class=\"text-blue-500 underline hover:text-blue-600\" href=\"https://cigsandredvines.blogspot.com/2002/10/interview-new-york-film-festival-q.html\">\"Interview: New York Film Festival Q&amp;A\"</a>). Blake produced his multimedia works—often dubbed \"moving\" or \"digital\" painting—by manipulating painted images with vector-based graphics (which employ mathematical formulas) and animation in AfterEffects. The resulting digital works seem to warp and melt in a blur of color and form. In addition to his contributions to this film, Blake designed <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" class=\"text-blue-500 underline hover:text-blue-600\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sea_Change_%28album%29#/media/File:Beckseachange.jpg\">the cover</a> for Beck's 2002 album <i>Sea Change</i> and the music video for the featured song <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" class=\"text-blue-500 underline hover:text-blue-600\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lmeag1rwQgo\">\"Round the Bend.\"</a></p>"}],"target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-01009/canvas/1#xywh=1288,119,472,848"},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-01009/canvas/1/2c88615b-fde9-42f5-8173-15de5d974c16","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2025-08-14T19:30:10.278Z","creator":"Olivia Flores","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>As composer Jon Brion studied Jeremy Blake's color fields and the way they blend together, he realized he could do something similar with the score and sound design (Movie List, \"Jon Brion on working with Paul Thomas Anderson and scoring Punch-Drunk Love\"). Everything in the film—image, sound, score, and so on—mutually influenced one another and ultimately generated a synesthetic work of art.</p>"}],"target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-01009/canvas/1#xywh=442,116,698,852"}]}]}]}